## Page Sections

### 1. Hero Section
- **Component**: `<Hero>` from `src/components/Hero.jsx`
- **Purpose**: Primary conversion area with main call-to-action
- **Content**:
  - Heading: "Protect Your Future with Confidence"
  - Tagline describing car and home insurance
  - Two CTA buttons:
    - "Sign Up Now" тЖТ navigates to `/signup`
    - "Get a Demo" тЖТ opens demo request modal

### 2. Features Section
- **Purpose**: Highlight key benefits of InsureCo
- **Components**: `<InfoCard>` from `src/components/InfoCard.jsx` inside a Carbon `Grid`
- **Content**: 4 feature cards
  - Comprehensive Coverage
  - Fast Claims Processing
  - 24/7 Support
  - Flexible Plans

### 3. Car Insurance Section
- **Component**: `<SplitHero>` from `src/components/SplitHero.jsx`
- **Props**: `imagePosition="right"`, `background="primary"`, `id="car-insurance"`
- **Content**: Car icon, heading, description, 4 feature bullets, "Learn More" button

### 4. Home Insurance Section
- **Component**: `<SplitHero>` from `src/components/SplitHero.jsx`
- **Props**: `imagePosition="left"`, `background="secondary"`, `id="home-insurance"`
- **Content**: Home icon, heading, description, 4 feature bullets, "Learn More" button

### 5. Testimonials Section
- **Purpose**: Build trust through customer reviews
- **Components**: Carbon `Tile` components inside a Carbon `Grid`
- **Data**: 3 static testimonial objects (quote, name, role)

### 6. Call-to-Action Section
- **Purpose**: Final conversion opportunity before the footer
- **Components**: Carbon `Button` inside a full-width styled `<section>`
- **Content**: "Ready to Get Started?" heading + "Get Your Free Quote" button тЖТ `/signup`

### 7. Footer
- **Component**: `<Footer>` from `src/components/Footer.jsx`
- **Purpose**: Navigation and legal links; always the last element on the page

---

## Modal Component

### Demo Request Modal
- **Trigger**: "Get a Demo" button in the Hero
- **Component**: Carbon `Modal`
- **Fields**: Full Name, Email Address, Phone Number, Message (optional)
- **Actions**: "Submit Request" (alert + close) / "Cancel" (close)
- **State**: Managed with `useState`

